{
  "texts": [
    "These benchmarks, however, are ill-suited for open-ended evaluation.",
    "Evaluation on CrowS-Pairs and StereoSet relies on comparing LLMs' log probabilities for a given sentence pair.",
    "BBQ and SeeGULL measure stereotypes in existing NLP tasks such as Question Answering or Natural Language Inference (NLI), while SoFa introduces a perplexity based metric.",
    "As LLMs are being integrated into search engines (Microsoft 2023; Nakano et al. 2021; Tong 2024), users might interact with them by querying.",
    "This creates the need for autocompletion-style benchmarks that assess harms beyond explicit toxicity (Gehman et al. 2020; Dhamala et al. 2021)."
  ]
}